This paper is primarily focused on face recognition using deep learning methods, which falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The paper also discusses the use of deep metric learning, which is a subfield of machine learning (cs.LG) that deals with learning similarity or distance metrics between data points. Additionally, the paper discusses the importance of data size and the number of patches, which are relevant to artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and multimedia (cs.MM) sub-categories. Finally, the paper evaluates its proposed method on the LFW dataset, which is a common benchmark dataset in information retrieval (cs.IR) research.
